  "prompt": "In no more than 200 words please describe a time you gave remarkable service to one of your customer?",
  "response": "During my tenure as a customer service representative for a tech company, I once assisted a frustrated customer whose software had failed during a critical business presentation. Understandably upset, they needed an immediate solution. I quickly diagnosed the issue, which involved an incompatibility with a recent update, and provided a step-by-step guide to bypass the problem temporarily. Recognizing the urgency, I also escalated the matter to our engineering team to develop a permanent fix.  \n\nTo ensure the customer felt supported, I followed up within the hour to confirm the workaround was successful and asked if they needed further assistance. When the permanent fix was ready, I personally called them to walk them through the update and offered a complimentary subscription extension as a gesture of goodwill.  \n\nThe customer was deeply appreciative, highlighting how the swift and empathetic response salvaged their presentation and reinforced their trust in our company. They later left a glowing review, praising the service and recommending us to their network. This experience reinforced the importance of proactive, compassionate problem-solving in delivering remarkable service.",
